WEBVTT

00:00.398 --> 00:01.697
<i>So here's what you missed on Glee:</i>

00:01.783 --> 00:02.750
<i>The New Directions! are headed to Nationals</i>

00:02.784 --> 00:04.051
<i>in beautiful Los Angeles,</i>

00:04.085 --> 00:05.419
<i>and Sue gave Mr. Shue an ultimatum that,</i>

00:05.453 --> 00:07.054
<i>if they don't win, the club is finished.</i>

00:07.088 --> 00:08.642
Michael William Schuster!

00:08.660 --> 00:10.246
<i>But he says he knows a
championship team when he sees one.</i>

00:10.247 --> 00:10.715
You guys are ready.

00:10.716 --> 00:11.652
<i>Although last time I counted,</i>

00:11.668 --> 00:12.623
<i>they don't even have enough members.</i>

00:12.624 --> 00:14.168
<i>They'd better scare up
three band members stat.</i>

00:14.370 --> 00:15.570
<i>Finn lead the Glee Club
to victory last year,</i>

00:15.604 --> 00:16.571
<i>but now they don't have a leader</i>

00:16.605 --> 00:17.539
<i>and they also don't have Rachel.</i>

00:17.573 --> 00:20.038
<i>Or Kurt. Or Santana.
Or Britney. Or Mercedes.</i>

00:20.045 --> 00:21.705
<i>Or Rory, the Irish kid. Where'd he go?</i>

00:21.785 --> 00:22.952
<i>And they're also up against
a performing arts school</i>

00:22.987 --> 00:24.220
<i>where they don't even take classes</i>

00:24.255 --> 00:26.745
<i>and they're all, like,
acrobats and contortionists.</i>

00:26.789 --> 00:28.573
<i>And that's what you missed on Glee.</i>

00:30.596 --> 00:31.703
(school bell ringing)

00:31.803 --> 00:33.237
(humming)

00:34.396 --> 00:36.096
Hey, you wanted to see me?

00:36.176 --> 00:37.977
Yeah. Have a seat.

00:39.479 --> 00:40.779
(clears throat)

00:40.814 --> 00:43.749
Um, I just want to let
you know that even though

00:43.783 --> 00:45.451
I've kind of, like, checked out of school

00:45.485 --> 00:46.685
since I'm not going to college,

00:46.720 --> 00:48.320
I'm totally committed
to Glee Club, you know.

00:48.355 --> 00:50.289
I've had Artie and Blaine
drilling me, like, nonstop

00:50.323 --> 00:52.124
on the rights and lefts
of the choreography,

00:52.158 --> 00:54.627
and I've recruited three hot
Cheerios! to get us to 12...

00:54.661 --> 00:57.696
You don't have to prove
yourself to me, Sam.

00:57.731 --> 01:00.366
Finn transformed this
club when he joined up.

01:00.400 --> 01:02.001
He wasn't just a male lead,

01:02.035 --> 01:03.836
he was the captain of the football team.

01:03.870 --> 01:05.538
He was the coolest kid in school.

01:05.572 --> 01:07.206
I mean, a real dude, you know?

01:07.240 --> 01:10.209
He was our secret weapon
at those competitions.

01:10.243 --> 01:12.378
Other schools might have
had their version of a Rachel

01:12.412 --> 01:14.547
or a Kurt, but no one had a Finn.

01:14.581 --> 01:16.549
Yeah, he... he made it seem pretty cool.

01:16.583 --> 01:17.883
When he recruited you,

01:17.918 --> 01:19.985
he wasn't just looking
for another voice in here.

01:20.020 --> 01:21.687
He was looking for someone

01:21.721 --> 01:23.889
to take his place after he graduated.

01:23.924 --> 01:27.860
Someone to help lead all
of these wonderful misfits.

01:27.894 --> 01:30.029
I'm not Finn, Mr. Shue.

01:31.231 --> 01:32.831
Finn was, like, a real leader, you know?

01:32.866 --> 01:34.934
And so are you.

01:34.968 --> 01:38.237
And I'm gonna need you to be
that guy when we get to L.A.

01:38.271 --> 01:40.172
The kids want you to be that guy.

01:40.207 --> 01:41.215
They're all waiting for you to see yourself

01:41.218 --> 01:43.375
the way they see you.

01:43.410 --> 01:45.878
The new kids love you,
and so do the older ones.

01:45.912 --> 01:49.348
I'm sure that everything is
gonna be fine once we get there.

01:49.382 --> 01:52.117
But if the time comes,

01:52.152 --> 01:53.719
and you need to step up,

01:53.753 --> 01:57.056
I'm gonna be counting
on you to get it done.

01:58.658 --> 01:59.725
They're here.

02:00.760 --> 02:01.894
Hey, guys.

02:01.928 --> 02:03.195
Good morning.

02:04.497 --> 02:06.632
How's it going, man?

02:06.666 --> 02:08.366
We just wanted to come in and say

02:08.401 --> 02:11.904
that, uh, Finn really cared about you guys.

02:11.938 --> 02:13.272
More than you know.

02:13.306 --> 02:15.674
Finn always said that winning nationals

02:15.709 --> 02:18.544
was the greatest
accomplishment of his life.

02:18.578 --> 02:22.314
But I honestly believe
that coaching you guys

02:22.349 --> 02:24.283
to winning would have
meant even more to him.

02:24.317 --> 02:26.418
BURT: Now, now we're not saying

02:26.453 --> 02:28.521
go out there and win it for Finn.

02:28.555 --> 02:30.256
That wasn't his style.

02:31.157 --> 02:35.461
Um, what Finn would have said was

02:35.495 --> 02:39.598
this is the time of your lives right now.

02:39.633 --> 02:42.735
You're never gonna forget it,

02:42.769 --> 02:45.504
and in a moment, it's all gonna be over.

02:45.539 --> 02:47.806
So no sad faces.

02:47.841 --> 02:49.742
No regrets.

02:49.776 --> 02:51.877
Just go out there and have a blast,

02:51.912 --> 02:55.114
and, you know, it'll be okay
if you won the damn thing.

02:55.148 --> 02:56.482
(laughter)

02:56.516 --> 02:58.417
And the best part about
it is that Burt and Carole

02:58.451 --> 03:00.452
have agreed to come with us as chaperones.

03:00.487 --> 03:03.689
(cheering)

03:03.723 --> 03:06.859
But I think before we go,
we need a little mood music

03:06.893 --> 03:07.927
to send us off.

